brewery.brewery_description:
Based on a 100-year-old family farm in Jindong (yeah, where the f*&^ is that?), Rocky Ridge is WA's proudly independent, fiercely passionate brewery. 

We're Australia's first and only Certified Sustainable and Carbon Neutral brewery, three-time Champion WA Large Brewery winners, and makers of over 500 unique beers.

We believe the best beer comes from bold ideas, sustainable practices, and genuine community connections. With venues in Jindong, Duncraig, Brunswick (VIC), and now Burswood, we're on a mission to make f*&^ing good beer without compromise while leaving a positive impact on people and planet.
Current venues: Jindong (Production Brewery), Duncraig, Brunswick and Burswood.

beer.beer_description:
GOOD ENERGY v5 | 7% | West Coast Juicy IPA ?

The fifth iteration of our legendary Rocky Ridge x Copper & Oak collab is here. Slightly tweaked, slightly evolved, but still the Juicy West Coast IPA fans have come to love.

Medium-bodied and punchy at 50 IBU, this beer balances juicy haze with crisp, clean bitterness. The finish is smooth and lingering, leaving your palate ready for the next sip.

The hop bill is a carefully curated mix of Motueka, NZH-106, Idaho 7 Dynaboost, Amarillo Cryo, and Sabro Cryo. Delivering tropical and citrusy notes with subtle complexity.

beer.beer_description:
Our first-ever collab with the east coast legends Hawkers, Hi Note is all about good vibes, sunny sips, and finishing the year on the highest of notes. This West Coast IPA is crisp, punchy, and infused with tropical optimism.

Burnished gold in the glass with a soft hop haze and a white crown, Hi Note greets you with candied lime, juicy tropical fruit, and a citrus-forward hop bouquet. The palate opens with a touch of malt sweetness, quickly followed by a mid-palate burst of tropical and citrus notes, with Skyfarm lime threading through like a zesty ribbon of sunshine. Medium bitterness keeps everything balanced, while the crisp, clean finish leaves you ready for the next sip.

beer.beer_description:
A beer with a statement to make. The Limit Does Not Exist! Brewed in collaboration with Pink Boots Society Australia, to raise funds and awareness for the incredible work they do supporting women in brewing. From scholarships and mentoring programs to education and networking events, Pink Boots empowers women to smash the beer glass ceiling.  

Using the Pink Boots special hop blend of Krush, Simcoe, Mosaic, and Chinook, plus locally grown Margaret River Nugget and extra Krush Hyperboost and Mosaic Hyperboost, its bursting with citrus, berries, and subtle herbal-woody layers. Medium body, smooth haze, and no hop or yeast bite make it utterly crushable, while a fruity finish lingers with low to medium bitterness.

items.badge_description: Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 255 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%.  Try 5 more for Level 52!

Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 220 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 45!

You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 50 different beers with the style of IPA - New England / Hazy, Pale Ale - New England / Hazy, IPA - Milkshake, or Pale Ale - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 11!

beer.beer_description:
Starting with a smooth, pillowy base of Certified Sustainable Pilsner Malt, rolled wheat, and oats, laying down the haze for a hop trio of Motueka, Citra, and the star of the show, Peacharine! The result? Waves of ripe peach, nectarine, citrus zest, and tropical fruit that explode out of the glass.

At 7%, this hazy IPA is juicy, soft, and packed with flavour, yet surprisingly easy to sink into. This is a beer for singing too loud, laughing too hard, and keeping life chill. Because shade never made anybody less hazy

beer.beer_description:
Karls had enough and hes taking 2025 with him. It feels appropriate to end the year with an absolutely bonkers fruit sour, packed with apricot, creamy vanilla, warming cinnamon, and a cheeky drizzle of maple syrup. Soft, frothy, and dangerously crushable, this one is perfect for sipping over the holiday break while you watch the year vanish into the rearview.

Pale apricot in colour with a soft frothy head, this sour hits your nose with ripe apricot, warming vanilla, a whisper of cinnamon, and a drizzle of maple syrup. The palate is a creamy, dreamy ice-cream-esque experience, balancing tartness with sweet indulgence.

items.badge_description: Marshmallow, chocolate, apple pie! Cakes and cookies catch my eye. Churn that butter, twist and shout. Put it in a pastry stout! Thats 20 different beers with the style of Stout - Pastry, Stout - Imperial / Double Pastry, or Sour - Smoothie / Pastry. Check-in to 5 more to get to Level 5.

beer.beer_description:
Lets talk hops  because if youve read this far lets face it that's why you're here. 

Eclipse. Idaho 7 Dynaboost. El Dorado Salvo. Cryopop. Vic Secret. Amarillo Cryo. Motueka. Rakau. Krush Hyperboost. Nelson SubZero Hop Kief. Rakau SubZero Hop Kief.
Hypercharged citrus. Stonefruit resin. Lush tropical overload. Dank edges wrapped in a velvet haze. Its bright. Its complex. Its stupidly drinkable! 

Built on a soft, layered malt base of Sustainable Pilsner, Cadiz Tritordeum, Triticale, Oats, Wheat and Chit, its juice with purpose, power and poise. This is top-shelf, peak-performance, unapologetically ridiculous IIIPA craft at its absolute best.

items.badge_description: While spontaneity can be fun, sometimes you want to make sure your adventure will rock. Checkout the menu at an Untappd Verified Venue before visiting and know exactly whats on tap! That's 60 check-ins at venue that is verified. Try 5 more for Level 13!
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 40 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 9! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

beer.beer_description:
CENTURION | Centennial | DIPA ?

Big, old-school, and unapologetically bold, Centurion is a 100-minute boil, 100 IBU, hop-smashing masterpiece. Every 10 minutes, 500g of Centennial T90 hit the kettle, followed by 5kg Centennial T90 and 1kg Centennial Dynaboost in the whirlpool a century of hops in every sense.

Clear amber with a white head, the aroma bursts with citrus and juicy stone fruit. Simpsons Medium Crystal malt gives body and a touch of sweetness, leading into a mid-palate citrus-forward hop punch and assertive, almost aggressive bitterness. Resin coats the mouth, leaving a long, lingering bitter finish that demands respect.

items.badge_description: Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!
Fifth in our series of Super Style badges, this one is dedicated to the beloved Imperial IPA, which ranked as the 3rd most checked-in style of 2021. AVAILABLE ONLY TO UNTAPPD INSIDERS

beer.beer_description:
Brewed in collaboration with the mad scientists at Ronin Fermentation Project, this turbo-charged, double dry-hopped danger dog is powered by a fluffy-soft malt base of Sustainable Pilsner Malt, Wheat, Rolled Wheat, and Oats. Pillowy? Yes. Punchy? You bet.

We hit it with a high-voltage combo of Rakau and Idaho 7 Cryo, then cranked the flavour, dialling the fruit energy to maximum zoomies with Skyfarm pineapple and mango terpenes. Tropical energy. Citrus crackle. Stonefruit sizzle.

beer.beer_description: Expect an opaque lupulin mist swirling in the glass, from which tropical fruit juice  mango, pineapple and orange - aromas rise. Such fruitiness continues through the full, almost creamy mouthfeel to the last sip, followed by a lasting alcohol warmth.
Medium body and viscosity. Yeast esters and pureed peach combine nicely for a very fruit forward aroma. Low bitterness and a creamy mouthfeel make this a great option for all levels of beer drinker.

Named for Our Brewmaster and Supervisor Ace the Brewery dog (Who also just decided he wants to be chief taste tester as well... Is there anything this bloke can't do?) Our take on the classic American Pale Ale, utilizing (See what I did there?) experimental hop Flinders. This bad boy has lashings of tropical fruit, citrus and lemongrass on the nose, backed by a subtle yet full body with a rounding, cleansing bitter finish.

Over 5 years of sour beer development have gone into this delicious fruit bomb.

Combining Passionfruit, Kiwi and Strawberry, Rock Candy is the perfect sour crusher!

Full bodied with a soft but robust mouthfeel, Rock Candy is fruit forward without compromising drinkability.

Pale copper with light hop haze. Aromas of pine, mango and passionfruit leap out of the glass. Pine and tropical fruits lead on the palate with a cracker base undercurrent. Bitterness builds with a mouth coating pine resin.

Rocky Ridges latest collaboration with Old Bridge Cellars land in the latter segment.

Not concerned with current trends, this duo has crafted a classic West Coast IPA that swells with citrus. While the referenced rock classic is in A minor, the beer is definitely in C, with Cascade, Centennial, Chinook and Columbus hops applied equally, and fresh hop flowers from the brewerys hop garden used for late additions and dry hopping. The effect is a citrus and pine mlange, on a lean and slightly opaque body, that drives the resiny dankness towards a dry coda.
Cracker malts with noble hops that give a herbaceous, fresh cut hay note. Firm cleansing bitterness enhances drinkability in our nod to the king of lagers.

Yo, we heard you like big dumb sours...We've got you covered with this rambunctious triple fruited imperial sour. Packed full of enough fruit to keep you buzzin' for a hot minute, there's only one thing you can do, get a mouthful of froooot.
Light golden haze with tropical hop aromas, pasionfruit, pineapple & stone fruit. This leads to a soft, chalky mouthfeel & rounded out with a light bitter finish.
Sticky date russian imperial stout with pecans. Collaboration with Get Chunky and Mane Liquor.
The first of our more experimental series, utilising 20kg of shredded and roasted coconut. Massive aromatics, silky smooth chocolate body and moreish finish.

Hops used in this one deliver rockmelon, sherbet, citrus and apricot with an interesting vegetal background character. Not to mention a forthright bitterness wherein a residual hop bite builds increasingly aggressive layers through each sip.

Were stoked to be a part of the Carwyn Canvent once again!  When the Bens reached out to us with the additional offer of collaborating with the legends at Bottle Logic, you better believe we jumped at the chance!  We put our collective thoughts together and came up with this crisp, resinous Christmas cracker of an IPA for you all to enjoy!  US and NZ hops drive the aromas while we fermented cool on a lager yeast to deliver an extra crisp body

beer.beer_name: Festivus For the Rest of Us
beer.beer_description: Collaboration beer between Rocky Ridge Brewing and Wild Hop Brewing. First brewed exclusively for Carwyn Cellars Canvent 2021.
The tropical hop punch delivered by the Galaxy and Ella hops coupled with the light malt backbone make the Session the ultimate thirst quencher.
Brewed in collaboration with LS Merchants, Rose Gose is sure to be the feelgood hit of spring!
Dank Side of the Moon- The ying to the yang of Pine on you crazy diamond. A Black IIPA, Double Dry hopped and bursting with aromatics.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
What happens when you bring together 18 of the best interstate and international producers into one brewery? You go and make a stoinker of a DIPA of course!

We have gone and thrown an absolute plethora of hops at this triple dry hopped collab to end all collabs. 
Stupid amounts of Wakatu, Strata, Meridian, Zamba, Sativa, NZH 101, NZH 107 & Loriel make up the gargantuan hop bill that is supported by a grain bill consisting of Pale Malt, Triticale, Rolled Wheat and Malted Wheat.

Peach, nectarine, white pepper, pine citrus. Light malt to start before an array of tropical fruits with a light piney under current giving way to firm bitterness.

Cleaner than a West Coast, crisper than a Lager, and dangerously drinkable.
Plum Lichtenhainer

Ryes Against the lack of bitterness! We are super excited about the release of this beer. 
The appearance is all haze but don't be fooled by it's charming good looks, this beast packs a punch.
Huge hop aromas are complimented by a subtle spice from the rye making this beer a very well balanced drinking experience.
Light bodied and easy drinking with low bitterness. All Aussie hops give off tropical fruits and a slightly herbaceous note. Super crisp finish and seriously moreish.
